<item>
            <title>[PAY-4174] Research and Implement Worldpay taxIdentificationType Requirement for Merchant Onboarding</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-4174</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Worldpay has introduced a new requirement for PayFac merchant onboarding. Effective &lt;b&gt;July 24, 2026&lt;/b&gt;, all new merchant onboarding requests must include the &lt;tt&gt;taxIdentificationType&lt;/tt&gt; field with a value of either &lt;tt&gt;SSN&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;EIN&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This spike will investigate the impact of this change on our merchant onboarding flow. The research should confirm the Worldpay API requirements, identify the affected application components, validate the business rules for &lt;tt&gt;SSN&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;EIN&lt;/tt&gt; usage, and provide a recommended implementation approach.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; Per the Worldpay communication, this requirement applies to newly onboarded merchants. Existing merchants on the Core/RAFT platform will be backfilled by Worldpay and do not require updates from PayFac clients.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="161831">PAY-4174</key>
