                                                            <comment id="99736" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2026 08:50:25 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3Aaa2afce0-9df4-4ba4-b955-cd538fded310&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;712020:aa2afce0-9df4-4ba4-b955-cd538fded310&quot; data-account-id=&quot;712020:aa2afce0-9df4-4ba4-b955-cd538fded310&quot; accountid=&quot;712020:aa2afce0-9df4-4ba4-b955-cd538fded310&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Swetha Bayya&lt;/a&gt; - This is the 3rd grader presentation of the rules, I like doing this for my personal use as it forces Claude to present it simply without a bunch of technical details that neither I or anyone else needs!  Hope this helps!  &lt;br/&gt;
Now, I will provide, in next comment, how QA can test it.&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Think of businesses in two buckets.

Bucket A &#8212; &quot;Could be a person&apos;s number&quot; businesses:
- A one-person business (sole proprietor)
- An LLC

Bucket B &#8212; everybody else:
- Corporations, partnerships, non-profits, government, or anything the system doesn&apos;t recognize

The rules

If it&apos;s in Bucket B &#8594; always EIN. No exceptions. A corporation gets a company number (EIN), period. It doesn&apos;t matter what tax number was typed in.

If it&apos;s in Bucket A &#8594; we have to check. A one-person business or LLC is allowed to use the owner&apos;s personal number (SSN), but it might also have its own company number (EIN). So the computer looks at the tax number that was sent and asks:

&#9614; &quot;Does this tax number exactly match the main owner&apos;s Social Security number?&quot;

- Yes, it matches &#8594; SSN
- No, it doesn&apos;t match &#8594; EIN

Two &quot;gotchas&quot; that make it say EIN even when you&apos;d expect SSN

1. The number has to be exactly 9 digits. A real SSN/EIN is 9 digits. If the tax number that came in is 8 digits, or 10, or has junk in it, the computer won&apos;t call it a match &#8594; EIN.
2. It only checks the main owner. A business can list several owners. The computer only compares the tax number to the first/primary owner&apos;s SSN. If the SSN that matches belongs to a different owner further down the list, it won&apos;t count &#8594; EIN.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                                                            <comment id="99741" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2026 08:59:57 -0700"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A56e71a0d-50b6-4231-892c-dac58ac29835&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;712020:56e71a0d-50b6-4231-892c-dac58ac29835&quot; data-account-id=&quot;712020:56e71a0d-50b6-4231-892c-dac58ac29835&quot; accountid=&quot;712020:56e71a0d-50b6-4231-892c-dac58ac29835&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Ana Oliva (contractor)&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=5bbba70ba334ec4325196e18&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;5bbba70ba334ec4325196e18&quot; data-account-id=&quot;5bbba70ba334ec4325196e18&quot; accountid=&quot;5bbba70ba334ec4325196e18&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Radhika Kandoori&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://wellfit.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3Aef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; data-account-id=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; accountid=&quot;712020:ef9caae6-9c72-4f4b-ad51-72da2faad9c6&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;Christopher Ariel Valenzuela Medina&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
Pretty straightforward test!  And I am certain you will find other edges to play with!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a Merchant Provisioning implementation &#8230;&lt;br/&gt;
Use the Postman scripts you already have to test this &#8230; you will need the create and the read&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;create - &lt;tt&gt;URL&lt;/tt&gt;/provisioning/create-sub-merchant&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Set up your payload with Legal Entity set up this way - notice I am using the randomSsn that the first principal uses (so they match)&lt;br/&gt;
Confirm you only have one principal and StakePercent is 100% &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That should create a &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&quot;taxIdentificationType&quot;: &quot;SSN&quot;,&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;Type&quot;: &quot;INDIVIDUAL_SOLE_PROPRIETORSHIP&quot;,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;OwnershipType&quot;: &quot;PRIVATE&quot;,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;TaxId&quot;: &quot;{{randomSsn}}&quot;,
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;After you create it, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;read - &lt;tt&gt;URL&lt;/tt&gt;/provisioning/retrieve-sub-merchant?wellfitSubMerchantId={{&lt;tt&gt;wellfitSubMerchantId}}FromTheCreate&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Look at the provider responses for the 2nd provider, that is CORE&lt;br/&gt;
See below - &quot;taxIdentificationType&quot;: &quot;SSN&quot;,&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;            &quot;responseCode&quot;: 10,
            &quot;responseDescription&quot;: &quot;Approved&quot;,
            &quot;validationException&quot;: null,
            &quot;metadataAsRaw&quot;: {
                &quot;correlationId&quot;: &quot;98372014-0e7f-4ca8-9e1d-f543717e1d54&quot;,
                &quot;id&quot;: null,
                &quot;subMerchant&quot;: {
                    &quot;uuid&quot;: &quot;bbc92a43-d3af-45bc-94c5-acd3c20ded5b&quot;,
                    &quot;chainCode&quot;: &quot;03540R&quot;,
                    &quot;federalTaxId&quot;: &quot;100338492&quot;,
                    &quot;taxIdentificationType&quot;: &quot;SSN&quot;,
                    &quot;legalName&quot;: &quot;BMRLE1029TQA&quot;,
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Now do a create with &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;Type&quot;: &quot;LIMITED_LIABILITY_COMPANY&quot;,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;OwnershipType&quot;: &quot;PRIVATE&quot;,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &quot;TaxId&quot;: &quot;{{randomTaxId}}&quot;,&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The read should provide a &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;taxIdentificationType&quot;: &quot;EIN&quot;,&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
